  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Cut the eggplant into 1-inch cubes and place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.",
    "Drizzle the eggplant with 1 tablespoon of olive oil and toss to coat evenly.",
    "Roast the eggplant in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes, or until it's charred and tender.",
    "Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until it's translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger and cook for another minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the roasted eggplant, clear honey, lemon juice, salt, black pepper, cumin seeds, and coriander powder to the skillet.",
    "Stir everything together and cook for 2-3 minutes, or until the flavors have melded together.",
    "Garnish with chopped fresh cilantro and serve hot."
  ],
